<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=necromancerbalance&message.id=3142#M3142">8</a> of 15
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 251 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<div></div><p>Could be easily made as difficult or as expensive as desired, the above was an example.</p><p>Quested 10-Slot container, or (Tradeskilled consumable) put:</p><p>1 x Pristine Soulstone<br>1 x Vial of Purified Mana<br>2 x Emerald<br>6 x Soul Orb</p><p>To create: Uncharged Essence Emerald</p><p>Cast a Level 70 spell: Imbue Essence Emerald (Obtained on its own via a Dark quest) to use 2000 mana per essence emerald we have a semi-involvedquest.</p><p>To be honest in roleplay the &quot;Sacrifice&quot; spell is a sham. I am a Guktan Wraith I don't want to ask a goody goody troll to &quot;consent&quot; to being sacrificed. The best sacrifices are those from unwilling victims. Those with real hate for you. All that energy focussed into an orb, that is true power. Not some being on bended knee begging for death, unless at the very end of torture.</p><p>I want them to submit to my will as I take their soul piece by piece and from that use them for MY own benefit. I want to create an &quot;Essence of weak and pathetic troll&quot; as the last glimpse in their anguished conscious mind beholds their life in the emerald.</p><p>Apart from a quest, which could be quite challenging to get a permanent container, or a more expensive (100-200pp per pop tradeskilled) we have something that will create EE's for about 330pp (minimum) add in consumable we have 500pp, which is about the price we have on DRo. Have all components farmable (and not foraged) so we have a 330pp cost for those willing to work at it. 500+pp for those that wish to buy all.</p><p>IMO I think 300pp cost all round with chance to be cheaper should be around the figure for this cost.</p><p>I could see a quest going this way...</p><p>Hail Priest of Luclin. Said priest is working on a Pristine Soulshard for use on creatures more powerful than Level 70. To do this he requires an Essence Emerald with the body parts and life force of 4 creatures. Collect 4 creatures tongues + 4 soul orb, into a box and combine. Give priest a Pristine Soulstone, Essence Emerald and the Soul Box.</p><p>Great explosion, discharged essence emerald. Would be fun if there was an AE around the NPC that would do 5000 damage or something in the guild lobby <img src='/i/smilies/16x16_smiley-happy.gif' width=16 height=16 border=0></p><p>Lots of subquest (where Imbue spell could be bestowed to recharge EE for later use), etc. Obtain more secure box (ala Glowing Box of Protection), subquest, more involved lining quest, etc etc. to finally create Luclin Enhanced Glowing Box of Protection, which is a permanent one or.... Tradeskill has an ablative metal container, which protects from explosion but is used in the combination.</p><p>Combine the labile souls of those you vanquish unwillingly into a Pristine Soulstone, add emerald and Vial of Purified Mana, and combine. The combination creates the Uncharged Essence Emerald, which then is charged to normal essence emerald via copious use of mana (2000).</p><p>I believe all of that is more than sufficient once you set your mind to it to create as many Essence Emeralds as you want for a very modest price, rather than having to rely on the good will of others (Does that scream necro to you... no!)</p>
								<p><div style="width: 100%; height: 120; overflow: hidden;">
								
							<hr><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=1281938&resize=true>Horcrux SoulImbiber</a><b> Guktan Grand Occultis</b>t<br><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=636624&resize=true>Corvard Pasodonia</a> <b>Prelate O'Brell</b><br><b>Druzzil Ro</b>
							</div>
								
