<BLOCKQUOTE>
<HR>
cfwmac007 wrote:<BR>
<DIV></DIV>
<P>i still contunuie my support of being a mana battary there are many necros that dont get the luxuary have being grouped with clerics with 10k mana pools and have enough mana regen augs to give a necro a run for his money with lich. Also as far as finding a place to solo that still gives good xp in the high 60's is almost imposible.. to many new zones have high mob populations...this kiss the idea of fear kitting, common mobs that can summon....no agro kitting, and mobs that hit so hard my pet is sent to next tuesday...so no pet tanking....lower zones often have to may mobs that are green to me or still take time to kill with kitting.&nbsp; i solo the crap out of murks in NC...but when it takes almost 7 of them to get 1% xp......its not worth it</P>
<P>and as far as the idea of sacing mobs...i did not mean for it to be used against raid mobs and such...just mosly trash mob and make the ee no trade...and for going to baz and buying the EE...same problem as getting one the standard way....NO MONEY....on povare EE's cost and arm and leg i have seen avarage price of 1 to 4k in the baz and finding someone want to get saced just for the hell of it does not happen often</P>
<P>and you have to remeber not everyone who plays a necro and post on the board are high end...and get to play with high end groups....and you were all in the same shoes at one time or other</P>
<P>&nbsp;</P><BR>
<HR>
</BLOCKQUOTE>
<P><BR>Dude.... if you want to be a mana battery I was never in your shoes. I've played with low mana pool clerics... but twitching is just about never the right solution. Killing stuff faster does far more benefit.&nbsp; Mana pools are much bigger today than they were previously - you can now see clerics in bazaar gear that have bigger mana pools than raid clerics used to. If it wasn't right twitching back then, it still isn't right twitching now. Mana pool size and regen have to simply be matched to content. If you can't group or raid there without twitching, you would be getting faster xp in slightly easier content and be better off raiding slightly easier mobs and gearing up.</P>
<P>Necros have some of the best pp farming abilities in the game. There are 101 things you can do to make pp. 1-4k is pretty expensive for an EE, not something you'd use every day, but if you really can't find it cheaper, that is still easily in range to have a few on you for real emergency situations. </P>
<P>There are tons of places to xp in the high 60s. No, you can't fear kite at that level.... but you should have stopped fear kiting in the early 50s anyway, since agro kiting is better xp anyway. No, you can't pet tank for xp - that's not what necros do. Pet tanking is for very very specific situations, not for just generating xp. I think you may have unreasonable expectations for the rate of xp - it is harder to get levels the higher you get. Twenty hours for a level isn't unheard of. And again, necros get some of the fastest xp of any class. You really don't have a thing to complain about there. </P>
<P>Not everyone who plays is a high end necro - but I think many have better math skills and more dedication, whether high end or not. You've got a good thing in your grasp and you are using it wrong and then complaining about it. </P>	
